                  <cell><fillin /></cell>
                </row>                
              </tabular>
            </table>

        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Use your work in <xref ref="T-ez-8a-1-2">Table</xref> to find the formula for <m>T_3(x)</m> that satisfies <m>T_3(0) = f(0)</m>, <m>T_3'(0) = f'(0)</m>, <m>T_3''(0) = f''(0)</m>, and <m>T_3'''(0) = f'''(0)</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
              Plot <m>f(x)</m>, <m>T_1(x)</m>, <m>T_2(x)</m>, and <m>T_3(x)</m> on the same axes, centered at <m>a = 0</m>.  What do you notice?
